# Git Sync Provisioning Wizard -- Cloud Agent E2E Testing

Drive the Grafana provisioning wizard through the browser using **computer use** (screenshot + mouse/keyboard actions). This rule is for Cursor Cloud Agents only. Local agents should use the `.cursor/skills/test-git-sync-provisioning/` skill instead.

## Prerequisites

### 1. Start Grafana

Grafana must be running before testing. Build and start both backend and frontend:

```bash
# Backend (first build ~3 min, hot-reload after)
make run &

# Frontend dev server (~45s first compile)
yarn start &
```

Wait for Grafana to be healthy before opening the browser:

```bash
# Poll until healthy (up to 5 min for first build)
for i in $(seq 1 60); do
  if curl -sf http://localhost:3000/api/health > /dev/null; then
    echo "Grafana is ready"
    break
  fi
  echo "Waiting for Grafana... ($i/60)"
  sleep 5
done
```

The feature toggles `provisioning` and `kubernetesDashboards` must be enabled. Add to `conf/custom.ini` before starting:

```ini
[feature_toggles]
enable = provisioning,kubernetesDashboards
```

### 2. Required Secrets

Secrets are configured in the Cursor dashboard and exposed as environment variables. Read them in bash with `echo "$VAR_NAME"`. **Do not reference `.env` files or `source load-env.sh`.**

| Environment Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT_REPO_URL` | GitHub repo URL for PAT flow (e.g., `https://github.com/owner/repo`) |
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT` | GitHub Personal Access Token |
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_APP_REPO_URL` | GitHub repo URL for GitHub App flow |
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_ID` | GitHub App ID (numeric) |
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID` | GitHub App Installation ID (numeric) |
| `GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` | PEM private key **content** (not a file path) |

Verify secrets are available before starting:

```bash
for var in GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT_REPO_URL GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT GIT_SYNC_TEST_APP_REPO_URL \
           GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_ID GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID \
           GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY; do
  if [ -z "${!var}" ]; then
    echo "ERROR: $var is not set"
    exit 1
  fi
  echo "OK: $var is set"
done
```

## Browser Startup & Login

1. Open the browser to `http://localhost:3000`
2. Take a screenshot. You should see the Grafana login page.
3. Click the username field. Type `admin`.
4. Click the password field. Type `admin`.
5. Click the "Log in" button.
6. If prompted to change password, click "Skip" or navigate directly to the wizard URL.
7. Take a screenshot to confirm you are on the Grafana home page.

## Cleanup Before Testing

Before running any flow, delete all existing test repositories and connections via API:

```bash
BASE="http://localhost:3000/apis/provisioning.grafana.app/v0alpha1/namespaces/default"
AUTH="admin:admin"

# Delete repositories first (must be deleted before their connections)
for name in $(curl -s -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/repositories" | jq -r '.items[].metadata.name'); do
  echo "Deleting repository: $name"
  curl -s -X DELETE -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/repositories/$name"
done

# Then delete connections
for name in $(curl -s -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/connections" | jq -r '.items[].metadata.name // empty'); do
  echo "Deleting connection: $name"
  curl -s -X DELETE -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/connections/$name"
done

echo "Cleanup complete."
```

## Overview

**Entry URL:** `http://localhost:3000/admin/provisioning/connect/github`

The wizard has 5 steps. The Next button text always shows the *next step's name* (e.g., "Configure repository", "Choose what to synchronize"), except on the last step where it says "Finish".

**Step heading format:** `{n}. {step title}` (e.g., "1. Connect", "2. Configure repository"). Always verify the step heading in a screenshot before interacting with the step's fields.

## PAT Flow

Use `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT_REPO_URL` and `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT`.

### Step 1: Connect

1. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/admin/provisioning/connect/github`
2. Take a screenshot. Wait until you see the heading "1. Connect" and the text "Connect with Personal Access Token".
3. Click the radio option labeled "Connect with Personal Access Token".
4. Click the Token input field (placeholder: `ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx`). Type the value of `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT`.
5. Click the Repository URL input field (placeholder: `https://github.com/owner/repository`). Type the value of `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_PAT_REPO_URL`.
6. Click the button labeled "Configure repository".

**Wait:** The button shows "Submitting..." during K8s reconciliation. Take screenshots every 5 seconds until the heading "2. Configure repository" is visible. Allow up to 30 seconds.

### Step 2: Configure Repository

1. Take a screenshot. Confirm the heading "2. Configure repository" is visible.
2. **Branch field** (first combobox, pre-filled with `main`): Click the "Clear value" button (X icon) next to the branch field to clear it. Click the branch combobox input. Triple-click or press Ctrl+A to select all text, then press Delete to clear. Type `agent-test`. Press Enter as a separate action (do not submit with the type action). The branch `agent-test` must already exist on the remote.
3. **Path field** (second combobox): Click the path combobox input. Type `dev`. Press Enter.
4. Click the button labeled "Choose what to synchronize".

**Wait:** Take screenshots every 5 seconds until the heading "3. Choose what to synchronize" is visible. Allow up to 30 seconds.

### Step 3: Choose What to Synchronize

The step loads asynchronously. Take screenshots until the loading text "Loading resource information..." disappears and the sync target cards are visible.

1. Take a screenshot to see available sync target cards.
2. Click the card labeled "Sync external storage to a new Grafana folder" (Folder mode).
3. A "Display name" input appears (placeholder: `My repository connection`). Click it and type a descriptive name (e.g., `PAT Test Repo`).
4. Click the Next button. Its text is either:
   - "Synchronize with external storage" -- if the repo has content
   - "Choose additional settings" -- if the repo is empty (skips step 4)

### Step 4: Synchronize

**Skipped** when both the repo is empty and no local resources need migrating. If skipped, proceed to Step 5.

1. Take a screenshot. Wait until the "Begin synchronization" button is visible (loading text: "Checking repository status...").
2. Click "Begin synchronization".
3. **Wait for sync completion:** The sync job runs asynchronously and can take seconds to minutes. **Take a screenshot every 10 seconds.** Wait until the "Choose additional settings" button is no longer grayed out / disabled. Do NOT blindly sleep -- always verify via screenshot.
4. Click the button labeled "Choose additional settings".

### Step 5: Additional Settings

1. Take a screenshot to see available settings (sync interval, read only, PR workflow, etc.).
2. Optionally configure settings. For a basic test, defaults are fine.
3. Click "Finish".
4. **Wait:** The page navigates to `/admin/provisioning/{repoName}`. Take a screenshot to confirm you see the repository settings page.

**PAT flow complete.** The repository is now configured and syncing.

## GitHub App Flow

Requires `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_APP_REPO_URL`, `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_ID`, `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID`, and `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`.

### Step 1: Connect -- GitHub App Variant

1. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/admin/provisioning/connect/github`
2. Take a screenshot. Confirm you see the heading "1. Connect". "Connect with GitHub App" should be selected by default.

**Creating a new connection:**

3. If no connections exist, "Connect to a new app" is auto-selected. Otherwise, click the radio option labeled "Connect to a new app".
4. Click the Title input (placeholder: `My GitHub App`). Type a descriptive name (e.g., `Test GitHub App`).
5. Click the App ID input (placeholder: `123456`). Type the value of `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_ID`.
6. Click the Installation ID input (placeholder: `12345678`). Type the value of `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID`.
7. **Private Key (PEM):** The PEM content is in the `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` environment variable. Write it to a temp file first, then paste it:
   ```bash
   # Write PEM to temp file and copy to clipboard
   echo "$GIT_SYNC_TEST_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY" > /tmp/gh-app-key.pem
   cat /tmp/gh-app-key.pem | xclip -selection clipboard
   ```
   Then in the browser: click the Private Key textarea (placeholder: `-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----...`). Press Ctrl+V to paste.
   If `xclip` is not available, use `xsel --clipboard --input` or type the PEM content directly into the textarea.
8. Click the "Create connection" button.
9. **Connection pending bug:** After creating the connection, the status shows "Pending" but the backend resolves within ~10 seconds. The UI does not auto-update. **Workaround:** Press Ctrl+R to reload the page, or navigate to `http://localhost:3000/admin/provisioning/connect/github` again. Then:
   - Click the radio option labeled "Choose an existing app".
   - Click the connection dropdown (placeholder: `Select a GitHub App connection`).
   - Take a screenshot. Select the connection you just created from the dropdown options. It should show "Connected".

**After connection is selected:**

10. The repository URL field becomes a combobox populated from the connection's repos.
11. Take a screenshot. Click the repository combobox. Type to filter for the repo matching `$GIT_SYNC_TEST_APP_REPO_URL`. Take a screenshot to see dropdown options. Click the matching option.
12. Click the button labeled "Configure repository".

**Wait:** Take screenshots every 5 seconds until the heading "2. Configure repository" is visible. Allow up to 30 seconds.

**Steps 2-5 are identical to the PAT flow above.**

## Gotchas

### Kubernetes Reconciliation Delays
Every Next button click that submits data triggers a K8s resource write + reconciliation. The UI shows "Submitting..." on the button. **Never click the next element until the new step heading is visible in a screenshot.** Always take a screenshot and verify the next step's heading before proceeding.

### FormPrompt (Unsaved Changes Dialog)
The wizard intercepts navigation when the form is dirty (during bootstrap and synchronize steps). If a browser dialog appears asking to confirm navigation, click "Leave" or accept the dialog.

### Loading States
Each step loads data asynchronously. Take a screenshot and check for these loading indicators before interacting with form fields:
- Bootstrap step: "Loading resource information..."
- Synchronize step: "Checking repository status..."

### Combobox Fields
Branch, path, and repository URL (in GitHub App mode) use Combobox components, not plain input elements. To interact:
1. Click the combobox to open the dropdown.
2. For **selecting from options**: type to filter, then click the matching option from the dropdown in the screenshot.
3. For **free-text entry** (e.g., a branch name not in the pre-populated list): click the "Clear value" button (X icon) if a value is pre-filled. Click the combobox. Triple-click or Ctrl+A to select all existing text. Press Delete. Type the new value. Press Enter. The dropdown may appear empty -- this is expected; Enter commits the typed value.

### Step Heading as Navigation Confirmation
The step heading format is `{n}. {title}` (e.g., "2. Configure repository"). Always verify the full heading with the step number in screenshots to confirm step transitions completed. Do not rely on partial text matches -- use the full heading like "3. Choose what to synchronize" to avoid false matches with sidebar labels.

### Button Disabled States
The Next button may be disabled when:
- Form validation fails (required fields empty)
- Data is loading
- On the synchronize step: until the sync job completes
- During submission ("Submitting..." state)

Always take a screenshot and verify the button appears enabled (not grayed out) before clicking.

### Screenshot Polling
For any wait longer than 5 seconds, take screenshots in a loop rather than sleeping blindly. Check the screenshot for the expected state before proceeding. This applies to:
- Step transitions after clicking Next
- Sync job completion on Step 4
- Connection status becoming "Connected" after creation

### Branch Must Exist
The `agent-test` branch must already exist on the remote repository. The wizard will error with `branch "X" not found` if it does not.

## Verification

After the wizard completes, verify the repository was created:

```bash
curl -s -u admin:admin \
  http://localhost:3000/apis/provisioning.grafana.app/v0alpha1/namespaces/default/repositories | \
  jq '.items[] | {name: .metadata.name, type: .spec.type, url: .spec.github.url}'
```

## Post-Test Cleanup

After testing, clean up all created resources:

```bash
BASE="http://localhost:3000/apis/provisioning.grafana.app/v0alpha1/namespaces/default"
AUTH="admin:admin"

# Delete repositories first (must be deleted before their connections)
for name in $(curl -s -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/repositories" | jq -r '.items[].metadata.name'); do
  echo "Deleting repository: $name"
  curl -s -X DELETE -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/repositories/$name"
done

# Then delete connections
for name in $(curl -s -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/connections" | jq -r '.items[].metadata.name // empty'); do
  echo "Deleting connection: $name"
  curl -s -X DELETE -u "$AUTH" "$BASE/connections/$name"
done

echo "Cleanup complete."
```

Verify cleanup:

```bash
curl -s -u admin:admin \
  http://localhost:3000/apis/provisioning.grafana.app/v0alpha1/namespaces/default/repositories | \
  jq '.items | length'
# Should return 0
```

## Element Reference

Organized by wizard step. No `data-testid` attributes exist -- use ids, roles, labels, and placeholders to find elements visually.

### Step 1: Connect

**Auth Type Radio Buttons:**
| Label | Value |
|---|---|
| "Connect with GitHub App" | `github-app` (selected by default) |
| "Connect with Personal Access Token" | `pat` |

**PAT Fields:**
| Field | ID | Placeholder |
|---|---|---|
| Token | `token` | `ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx` |
| Repository URL | `repository-url` | `https://github.com/owner/repository` |

**GitHub App Mode:**
| Label | Value |
|---|---|
| "Choose an existing app" | `existing` |
| "Connect to a new app" | `new` |

**GitHub App -- New Connection Fields:**
| Field | ID | Placeholder |
|---|---|---|
| Title | `title` | `My GitHub App` |
| App ID | `appID` | `123456` |
| Installation ID | `installationID` | `12345678` |
| Private Key (PEM) | `privateKey` | `-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----...` |

**GitHub App -- Existing Connection:**
| Element | Details |
|---|---|
| Connection Combobox | Placeholder: `Select a GitHub App connection` |
| Repository Combobox | Populated from connection's repos after selection |

**Buttons:**
| Button Text | Context |
|---|---|
| "Create connection" | GitHub App new mode only |
| "Configure repository" | Next button (form submit) |

### Step 2: Configure Repository

| Field | Type | Placeholder |
|---|---|---|
| Branch | Combobox (first on page) | `main` |
| Path | Combobox (second on page) | (empty) |

**Button:** "Choose what to synchronize"

### Step 3: Choose What to Synchronize

**Loading indicator:** "Loading resource information..."

**Sync Target Cards:**
| Label | Description |
|---|---|
| "Sync all resources with external storage" | Instance mode -- syncs everything |
| "Sync external storage to a new Grafana folder" | Folder mode -- scoped sync |

**Folder mode field:** Display Name (ID: `repository-title`, placeholder: `My repository connection`)

**Buttons:**
| Text | Condition |
|---|---|
| "Synchronize with external storage" | Repo has content |
| "Choose additional settings" | Repo is empty (skips step 4) |

### Step 4: Synchronize

**Loading indicator:** "Checking repository status..."

| Element | Text |
|---|---|
| Begin Sync button | "Begin synchronization" |
| Next button | "Choose additional settings" (enabled after sync completes) |

### Step 5: Additional Settings

| Field | Type | Default |
|---|---|---|
| Sync Interval | Number input (placeholder: `60`) | 60 seconds |
| Read Only | Checkbox | unchecked |
| PR Workflow | Checkbox ("Enable pull request option when saving") | unchecked |
| Push to Branch | Checkbox | unchecked |
| Dashboard Previews | Checkbox (GitHub-only) | unchecked |
| Webhook URL | Text input (placeholder: `https://grafana.example.com`) | empty |

**Button:** "Finish" (navigates to `/admin/provisioning/{repoName}`)

### Step Headings

| Step | Heading |
|---|---|
| authType | "1. Connect" |
| connection | "2. Configure repository" |
| bootstrap | "3. Choose what to synchronize" |
| synchronize | "4. Synchronize with external storage" |
| finish | "5. Choose additional settings" (or "4." if sync was skipped) |

Note: If the synchronize step is skipped, the finish step becomes step 4 instead of 5.
